about 2000 people were urged to leave their 
homes monday after authorities found a liquid they thought was 
nitroglycerin in a house where officers earlier responded to a 
domestic dispute 
authorities also evacuated residents along a threemile route 
where a truck would carry the material out of this western ohio 
city of 20000 people 
michael hemm public information officer for the city said fbi 
tests indicated that the substance in the two 16ounce softdrink 
bottles could be nitroglycerin 
the slightest friction such as the removal of a cap can 
detonate it hemm said 
police arrested an occupant of the home dana taylor 25 and 
charged him with possession of a dangerous ordnance hemm said 
taylor whom police said had experimented with explosives before 
was held monday in the miami county jail 
about 2000 residents in 500 homes were urged to leave the area 
said police chief donald white officials werent able to say how 
many actually left but the evacuation area appeared empty 
about 100 people in this town 30 miles north of dayton ended up 
at an evacuation center at an elementary school said lucy fess 
executive director of the miami valley chapter of the american red 
cross 
hemm said fbi agents tested a syringe and shot glass containing 
sawdust in the basement both tested positive for nitroglycerin he 
said however the tests are not foolproof 
he said some flammable materials were removed from the house in 
the afternoon but the substance suspected of being nitroglycerin 
remained 
safety officials planned to use a dump truck filled with sand to 
take the chemical to a gravel pit outside of the city 
brad leffel 32 a neighbor said police arrived at taylors 
house shortly after midnight talked with him and entered the house 
after he left 
about seven hours later leffel said police came to his door and 
told him the neighborhood was being evacuated because of some 
explosive chemicals nearby 
i had no idea it was next door leffel said i took my 
time its got me thinking 
