the flap over an adamandevestyle motel 
mural has ended with the artist painting a branch over a pair of 
naked backsides that offended the citys mayor 
but artist steve kroeger had the last laugh sunday as he touched 
up the mural at the sunray lodge motel 
since city officials had also asked for children to be added in 
keeping with hollywoods family image kroeger obliged by painting 
one in the coppertone girl bare derriere and all 
the controversy began thursday when mayor sal oliveri asked that 
the bare bottoms of the adults be covered because it was offensive 
the 8foottall by 24footlong mural showed a rear view of a 
couple seated on a deserted beach and gazing into each others eyes 
oliveri said later he found nothing offensive about the bare 
bottom of the coppertone girl which is displayed on a billboard 
eight blocks away 
kroeger 34 originally refused to change the mural 
would they have put bathing suits on a rubens he asked last 
week 
but the artist said he added the branches and little girl to 
address the citys concerns and to avoid trouble for motel owner 
doris ouellet 
i am just complying with city officials he said they 
requested a child and a dog and thats what they got 
ms ouellet the owner of the motel laughed when she saw little 
miss coppertone 
i like it she said i didnt know he was going to put 
that in the picture i dont think its offensive 
ms ouellet said she had received about 50 calls in favor of the 
original mural with only two residents agreeing with the mayor 
that it should be toned down 
oliveri said sunday he was pleased that kroeger had cooperated 
this is very interesting he took a nude mural and put a 
child in it it changes the flavor in it a bit it seems he is 
cooperating what can i say 
