the lure is the montgomery gi bill under which participants can 
receive a 250 monthly stipend over three years of college 
while sailors can leave the service after two years of active 
duty under the program they must stay serve an additional six 
years with the nondrilling naval reserve 
the program was created in response to congressional calls for 
military spending cuts and leaner armed forces 
were looking for high school graduates boorda said 
were looking for quality people but also people who may not 
