<TEXT>
here is a look at how the soviet unions view of a 
united germanys military allegiance has changed since fall 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
nov 15 shortly after the berlin wall is opened and in the 
middle of east germanys political turmoil president mikhail s 
gorbachev says unification is not a matter of topical politics 
and to even discuss it is to interfere in germans internal affairs 
feb 10 west german chancellor helmut kohl visits moscow 
afterward he says he has received assurances from gorbachev that 
the soviet union will respect the german peoples wish to live as 
one nation 
feb 14 meeting in ottawa the united states and its major 
european allies reach agreement on a twostage formula for 
unification 
march 6 gorbachev says a united germanys membership in nato is 
absolutely out of the question the soviet union seeks a 
neutral germany 
april 6 after three days of talks between foreign minister 
eduard a shevardnadze and us officials in washington secretary 
of state james a baker iii says the soviet union is dropping its 
demand that germany be neutral but still opposes nato membership 
april 29 east germanys prime minister lothar de maziere 
meets with gorbachev and says gorbachev still opposes nato 
membership for a united germany 
june 6 shevardnadze and baker meet in copenhagen to discuss a 
ninepoint us plan to meet soviet security concerns about a 
united germany shevardnadze says the soviet union cannot agree to 
all parts of it 
june 12 gorbachev says the soviet union might accept an 
undefined associate membership in nato for a united germany if 
nato is transformed from its cold war stance against the soviet 
union west germany and its allies reject the idea 
monday gorbachev and kohl announce that a united germany may 
choose whatever alliance to which it wants to belong clearing the 
way for nato membership 
</TEXT>
