of whitewright texas 
the church is suing the sister and brother of the officer the 
late joe t meador to recover the treasures 
maurice said officials have no clear idea of how many other 
works were allegedly looted from germanys artitistic heritage in 
the final months of the war 
the problem up to now is that we had two states and it wasnt 
easy to speak with east germany maurice said now this is 
easier 
maurice spoke after attending a twohour meeting to dicuss 
coordinated approaches toward retrieving lost german art also 
attending the meeting was a ministry of culture representative from 
east germany which is expected to formally unite with its western 
neighbor in december 
the new database is to be established in berlin and collect 
information from museums churches and other institutions 
throughout the two germanys maurice said the database will 
compare preworld war ii inventories with current records in an 
attempt to get a complete picture of what is missing he said 
