here is the statement by west 
german chancellor helmut kohl during a live news conference monday 
from the soviet union on the results of his talks with soviet 
leader mikhail s gorbachev 
mr president ladies and gentlemen this press conference 
concludes a twoday encounter between president gorbachev and 
myself an encounter that i think in the history of 
germansoviet relations produced a new high point that covers the 
depth and the intensity of our talks in moscow in the airplane and 
here in the homeland of president gorbachev i understand this 
invitation in his homeland as a very special gesture our talks 
were marked by the greatest openness and mutual understanding and 
personal sympathy 
but what was special in the significance of this encounter lies 
in the results 
we are in agreement that in central issues broadranging 
progress could be reached 
this breakthrough was possible because both sides are aware that 
in germany and in europe and in the soviet union historical 
transformations are taking place that also places special 
responsibility on us 
as for the results of the talks i can note 
president gorbachev and i are clear that the germansoviet 
relationship is of central importance for the future of our peoples 
and for the fate of europe we agreed to conclude immediately 
after the unification of germany a comprehensive and fundamental 
bilateral treaty that regulates our relationship on a longterm and 
goodneighborly basis such a treaty should include all areas 
political relationships as well as the security of both sides 
economy culture science and technology visitor exchanges as well 
as many other things the goal of this is to bring our relationship 
on the basis of stability verifiability trust for the future 
our talks served to clarify basic questions that are being 
negotiated in the framework of the twoplusfour talks we have 
stressed the agreement that was reached at the meeting of the six 
foreign ministers at the twoplusfour talks in june in berlin 
namely that the twoplusfour talks should be concluded in a time 
frame so that the results can be presented to the csce summit in 
november in paris i can today with satisfaction and agreement with 
president gorbachev state 
1 the unification of germany comprises the federal republic of 
germany the german democratic republic and berlin 
2 when unification is accomplished the rights of the four 
powers and responsibilities will be completely removed so that a 
unified germany at the time of its unification receives its full 
