one sunday 20 years ago former beatle paul 
mccartney and his wife linda looked out their kitchen window as 
they ate lunch and saw their sheep in the field it was the last 
time they ate meat 
if animals could speak i think theyd tell us not to eat 
meat linda mccartney said we are such a pompous race of 
humans were so destructive so sad people dream of heaven and 
you know were living in heaven but we make it hell 
her familys change in diet was influenced more by animal rights 
than by health but whatever the motivation mccartney preaches 
vegetarianism to that end she has written linda mccartneys 
home cooking already published in england and to be issued oct 
31 in this country by arcade publishing 2495 
i did the cookbook for one reason i love animals and to pass 
on the recipes to my kids and friends mccartney said from new 
jersey where she was with her husbands band at a stop on a world 
tour 
even on the road which is where the mccartneys have been for a 
year no meat or fish is served to the 180 people on the touring 
staff 
this whole tour is vegetarian and those who at first were 
skeptical have been converted she said 
people think of vegetarians as cranks they eat radishes and 
lettuce said mccartney who calls herself an instinctive peasant 
cook they dont realize you eat better as a vegetarian nothing 
suffers and you eat better you only cut out decaying flesh 
many of her friends had doubts but she and her family are 
healthy and friends who give up meat soon say they feel better 
she said 
but its not an easy change 
at first mccartney said she ate lots of quiches and macaroni 
and cheese at restaurants the choices were ratatouille or 
omelets then she began cooking with soybean imitation meats 
called texture vegetable protein now she uses much less of that 
and relies more on produce legumes and dairy products 
tvp sold in health food stores and some supermarkets is shaped 
like various meat products bacon burgers sausage and tastes 
exactly like meat said mccartney who added she has fooled many 
guests with it 
she suggests tvp is a good way to help convert a family to 
vegetarianism 
everybody bases their meal around a chop or a leg or a 
thigh and with tvp no one will think somethings missing she 
said 
in her book mccartney adapts vegetarianism to a decidedly 
british eating style with a proper english breakfast of vegetable 
sausages alongside fried eggs a festive sunday roast made from 
vegetable burgers and sausages with stuffing a suetfree christmas 
pudding and even a shepherds pie without beef 
i havent written this book in order to be acclaimed as a 
great cook like everyone ive had my share of disasters in the 
kitchen im simply doing it for the animals she wrote in her 
introduction 
most of the more than 200 recipes in the book are geared toward 
beginners they appear simple to prepare and were chosen from 
mccartneys years as a home cook yes although she surely can 
afford to stay out of the kitchen mccartney said she and her 
family paul plus four children have always spent a lot of time 
there 
mccartney even discusses ways to involve reluctant husbands and 
children in food preparation paul bakes bread 
ive never had a cook ive never had a nanny either i love 
my kids im sort of very womanly that way said mccartney who 
also is a photographer and plays keyboards with her husbands band 
vegetarianism takes a sense of awareness she said mccartney 
grew up a real meat eater never connecting the horses she 
loved with the horsemeat that was fed to her dogs 
i think were going through a food revolution and people will 
realize that meat is disgusting or i should say flesh is 
disgusting we cover everything up we call pig a ham 
humans should take their cue from animals such as gorillas or 
elephants she said strong animals dont eat meat i think we 
have a whole false thing about meat 
