lower level 
the main altar directly above bethlehem chapel was built next 
then came the choir with its richly carved wood and the south and 
north transepts which intersect the nave at right angles to form 
the shape of a cross 
construction stopped in 1977 due to the shortage of money work 
resumed in 1980 after a new bishop and dean the right rev john 
thomas walker started a fundraising drive and ordered stringent 
economies cutting back on heat reducing staff and turning the 
