critics can be found in the strangest 
places try the back seat of chrissie hyndes car 
one evening this spring the pretenders leader popped a working 
tape of her bands new album into the cassette deck of her car she 
drove in circles around regents park in london trying to decide if 
the running order of the songs made musical sense 
hyndes 5 and 7yearold daughters were dozing in the back seat 
or so she thought suddenly a small voice peeped up from behind 
mummy her youngest daughter asked can we hear sense of 
purpose again 
smart kid the longingforlove ballad is probably the best of 
12 songs on packed the first new pretenders album since 1986 
since the early 1980 release of a debut pretenders album that 
has aged into a classic hyndes life and band have changed 
considerably her music hasnt 
hynde is the only constant in the pretenders life over the 
years shes seen two band members die drugrelated deaths fired a 
drummer and seen another guitarist quit to join paul mccartneys 
band 
she insists the pretenders are still a band although she and 
drummer blair cunningham are currently the only members the search 
is on for a guitarist and bass player in time for a tour of the 
united states expected to start in late september 
hyndes two daughters are aware of what their mother does for a 
living but the car ride was the first time she remembered them 
reacting to her work they usually listen to their nannys opera or 
classical recordings 
i feel like im more humanitarian because of my relationship 
as a mother she said during a recent interview when i walk 
through central park i want to be seen in the community as a 
mother i dont want to be seen as a celebrity or a show business 
figure 
her children are the product of relationships with fellow 
musicians ray davies of the kinks and jim kerr of simple minds she 
married kerr but theyre now separated 
motherhood hasnt necessarily softened the outspoken woman who 
wrote tattooed love boys just ask her opinion about the 
nations drug war more about that later 
but the differences in her life have obviously changed her 
approach to work its the chief reason why there was a fouryear 
gap between pretenders albums 
since ive been in the hotel the past week i wake up at 6 
oclock in the morning and the first thing i do is reach for a 
guitar said hynde who was over from london for a publicity tour 
