<TEXT>
 
the adventures of ford fairlane 
joe silver proves the ideal force to bring andrew dice clay to 
the screen the producer of the die hard lethal weapon and 
predator movies is of course the king of the lowest common 
denominator he has an absolute knack for spending megabucks on 
films that are full of flash with no redeeming social values 
the adventures of ford fairlane fits neatly into this silver 
pattern expensive cars explode a luxury beach house blown up 
pointblank killings fights atop a tall building heavy metal 
sound track language that would make a rap singer blush 
all this plus the dicemans brand of comedy no he doesnt 
parade his notorious gay and female putdowns but the level of 
humor remains below the belt with matching nomenclature lots of 
oral sex jokes spoken and visual colorful asides to set the 
frathouse boys sniggering 
theres a plot sort of clay is ford fairlane an la private 
eye who specializes in rock music cases a dullwitted philip 
marlowe he bumbles his way through murders drug deals and 
highlevel deceptions is the music world really that venal 
fairlane is assisted by his sleek secretary lauren holly and a 
ditzy groupie brandon call and beset by a host of opponents 
including an oily executive wayne newton his slinky exwife 
priscilla presley and a cockney crazy robert englund aka 
freddy krueger of the nightmare on elm street pictures 
the taste of the film is sometimes astonishing a college 
sorority is portrayed as some kind of sex academy a long sequence 
takes place in a cemetery where a limo and a hearse stage a 
murderous chase scattering mourners and toppling gravestones 
and what about andrew dice clay in his starring debut he has 
had smaller film roles he seems to have studied the howard 
cossell school of elocution pausing between each word 
his expressions range from distaste to smirk there may be more 
fords in his future but his versatility remains unanswered 
finnish director renny harlin who also directed die hard 2 
knows how to maintain a frenzied pace daniel waters james cappe 
and david arnott labored on the mindless script apparently working 
from the joel silver handbook steve perry coproduced 
the adventures of ford fairlane is a 20th century fox 
release rated r for all the above reasons and more running time 
96 minutes 
by bob thomas associated press writer 
</TEXT>
