here is a list of historic dates for the dow 
jones industrial average of 30 stocks 
1896 first appears in the wall street journal 
jan 12 1906 closes above 100 for the first time at 10025 
sept 3 1929 reaches its closing peak for the bull market of 
the 1920s at 38117 less than two months before the great crash 
oct 28 1929 plummets 3833 points the worst drop on record 
until 1986 cutting nearly 13 percent of the averages value 
closing at 26064 
july 8 1932 closes at its depression low of 4122 having 
fallen 89 percent in less than three years 
march 12 1956 closes above 500 for the first time at 50024 
jan 18 1966 reaches 1000 for the first time in midsession 
but drops back to close at 99420 
nov 14 1972 closes above 1000 for the first time at 
100316 
jan 11 1973 peaks at 105170 
dec 6 1974 closes at a 12year low of 57760 ending the 
worst bear market since the 30s 
april 27 1981 closes at an eightyear high of 102405 
aug 12 1982 closes at a twoyear low of 77692 just prior 
to the start of a historic rally 
aug 17 1982 rises 3881 points to 83124 in its 
thenlargest oneday gain as the long rally begins on wall street 
dec 11 1985 increases 1250 points to close at 151170 its 
first finish above 1500 
jan 8 1987 breaks the 2000 level for the first time rising 
830 to 200225 
jan 23 1987 plunges to end day down 4415 points at 
210152 after being up 64 points at midafternoon nyse volume 
hits a record 30239 million july 17 1987 climbs 1307 to 
251004 closing above 2500 for the first time 
oct 16 1987 plunges 10836 points to 224673 falling more 
than 100 points for the first time 
oct 19 1987 dives a record 50800 points to 173874 a drop 
of 226 percent that dwarfs the drop on oct 28 1929 in the 
markets great crash 
oct 21 1987 soars a record 18684 to 202785 a climb of 
101 percent in the second day of the rebound from the oct 19 
collapse the broader market also rebounds 
feb 4 1988 falls 563 to 205786 the same day new york 
stock exchange announces it will experiment with a 50point 
collar on program trading the exchange bars the use of its 
computers for index arbitrage on days the dow rises or falls 50 
points or more from its previous close 
feb 8 1988 falls 1476 to 189572 its low for the year 
march 25 1988 closes down 4492 to 197895 the 50point 
collar is triggered on the down side for the first time during 
the session 
april 6 1988 jumps 6416 to 206167 triggering the collar 
on the up side for the first time 
jan 24 1989 gains 3804 to 225643 regaining its oct 16 
1987 level for the first time since the black monday crash on oct 
19 1987 
oct 9 1989 gains 589 to 279141 its high for the year 
oct 13 1989 falls 19058 to 256926 on friday the 13th 
selloff sparked by failure of ual corp buyout group to get 
financing 
oct 16 1989 gains 8812 to 265738 in rally led by dow 
industrials 
jan 2 1990 gains 5695 to 281015 reaching a record high 
for the first time since the oct 13 plunge 
jan 12 1990 falls 7146 to 268921 on worries about higher 
inflation and earlier declines in the tokyo and london stock 
markets 
jan 22 1990 falls 7745 to 260045 putting the dow 
industrials 747 percent below its record high of jan 2 
may 11 1990 rises 6307 to 280158 in rally sparked by 
economic reports suggesting mild inflation 
may 14 1990 gains 1995 to 282153 topping the jan 2 
record close for the first time 
may 29 1990 jumps 4957 to record 287049 
june 1 1990 gains 2431 to 290097 first close above 2900 
july 13 1990 crosses 3000point level during the session for 
the first time before slipping back in later trading finishes at 
298020 a new record high 
