mcdonnell douglas corp announced plans monday 
to reduce its workforce by up to 11 percent about 17000 jobs and 
cut other costs in an effort to shore up the aerospace giants 
sagging bottom line 
john f mcdonnell chairman and chief executive officer said 
the measures should save the company more than 700 million this 
year or about 5 percent of annual expenses and put the nations 
largest defense contractor on very solid footing 
he said the company has to become more efficient and profitable 
in order to ensure that its record backlog of commercial jet orders 
and other business opportunities were part of a bright future not 
a nagging nightmare 
we tried to work it without having significant job reductions 
but in the final analysis we had to come to this mcdonnell told 
a news conference 
mcdonnell douglas stock fell 250 to 4237 a share on the new 
york stock exchange 
company officials had said in june that they planned substantial 
layoffs although some securities analysts and union officials said 
the cuts were a little deeper than they expected 
weve seen a lot of changes at mcdonnell douglas and most of 
them have been rather ineffectual but positive effects from this 
plan should start showing up right away and thats when well 
become believers said paul nisbet a stock analyst for 
prudentialbache securities inc in new york 
