and at the same time newer programs are incurring cost growth 
also the effort to turn around douglas aircraft is unfinished 
harris said 
the company expects to eliminate between 14000 and 17000 jobs 
through layoffs and attrition mcdonnell said the bulk of the cuts 
will be made in st louis and long beach calif 
about 4500 jobs will be cut in the st louis area where 
mcdonnell employs about 40500 workers and does much of its defense 
work about 8000 jobs will be cut in long beach where the company 
employs 47000 and makes commercial aircraft and does some defense 
work 
another 800 jobs will be trimmed at a helicopter operation in 
mesa ariz and another 1000 jobs will be eliminated elsewhere in 
the country the company said 
when attrition and job elimination are included the company 
said up to 17000 positions could be trimmed under the plan 
the costcutting plan also includes reduced capital budgets 
significant cuts in budgets for travel consultants advertising 
and other support activities restrictions on overtime and a 50 
percent reduction in company contributions to the salaried savings 
plans 
mcdonnell said job fairs resume services and counseling would 
be offered to help laid off workers find new jobs 
