<TEXT>
rjr nabisco inc announced monday the details of 
a 69 billion recapitalization plan the company says will include 
the retirement of more than 3 billion in junk bonds and a 115 
billion bridge loan 
the recapitalization is aimed at reducing rjr nabiscos most 
expensive debt leaving the firm less vulnerable to the problems 
that have undermined other debtburdened companies over the past 
year 
under the plan rjr nabiscos debt will be reduced to less than 
20 billion from the current level of approximately 23 million 
said karl von der heyden the companys executive vice president 
and chief financial officer 
the recapitalization includes a previously announced 17 
billion cash infusion by kohlberg kravis roberts amp co the 
investment firm that engineered the record 2453 billion leveraged 
buyout of rjr nabisco last year kohlberg kravis said last month it 
planned to recapitalize the food and tobacco company but released 
few details of the plan 
the plan will be financed with the 17 billion from kohlberg 
kravis plus 225 billion in new bank loans the loans are expected 
to carry interest rates of 12 percent to 13 percent compared with 
the 16 percent to 17 percent rates that rjr nabisco junk bonds will 
carry 
rjr nabisco plans to repurchase at least 51 percent of its junk 
bonds known as subordinated exchange debentures with a maturity 
date of 2007 von der heyden said in a telephone interview 
the company also expected to retire at least 85 percent of junk 
bonds called senior converting debentures that are due in 2009 up 
to 85 percent of these securities will be exchanged for cash and a 
new issue of preferred stock in rjr nabisco with additional bonds 
possibly being acquired for cash von der heyden said 
after the recapitalization we will probably have something in 
excess of 3 billion of those two issues out of the 7 billion 
currently outstanding von der heyden said 
rjr nabisco said it hoped to complete the recapitalization by 
next april 
the company also announced it was resetting the interest rates 
on the junk bonds from the current 1407 percent to 17 percent for 
the subordinated exchange debentures and 17375 percent for the 
senior converting debentures 
by the terms under which the bonds were issued rjr nabisco had 
to reset the interest rate to make up for any price declines in the 
bonds because bond prices and interest rates move inversely and 
the market price for the securities has declined since their issue 
the company had to offer a higher rate at the reset 
the recapitalization also will allow rjr nabisco to repay the 
115 billion bridge loan used to complete the leveraged buyout 
in return for its 17 billion cash infusion kohlberg kravis 
will receive a new issue of common stock in rjr nabisco valued at 
625 a share rjr nabisco said kohlberg kravis also was 
exchanging 200 million of its own bridge loan to rjr nabisco for 
200 million in preferred stock 
von der heyden said rjr nabisco planned to reduce its debt load 
steadily during the next few years one of the things that will 
help us is were retiring a lot of junk debt he said 
after this recapitalization is completed the company will 
consider further debt retirement but this will not come up for 
quite a while von der heyden said 
we will always look at ways to bring down our effective 
interest rates and try to tackle the most expensive debt first 
he said referring to the remaining junk bonds 
he noted that junk bond debt cannot be retired without the 
agreement of rjr nabiscos bankers the companys bank loans have a 
higher repayment priority than do junk bondholders 
</TEXT>
